    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This FD3S chassis features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering a seamless power transition via the secondary actuator at 4,500 RPM. The drivetrain is anchored by a 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution during corner exit. The suspension remains true to its heritage with lightweight aluminum double-wishbones, providing exceptional feedback through the hydraulic rack-and-pinion steering. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full 'rat's nest' vacuum line simplification and a cooling system overhaul with an upgraded aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads. While the aesthetic reflects its age, the mechanical synchronization and compression across both rotors are within nominal operating specs, making this a purist's driver.",
